The paper discusses the challenges of managing and extracting knowledge from big linked data and knowledge bases from different domains, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The proposed framework also involves machine learning techniques for efficient knowledge discovery, which aligns with the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of semantic methods, which is a common topic in the sub-category of semantic web (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of accurate and efficient knowledge discovery, which is a key aspect of information retrieval (cs.IR).
